  <static seed="1613" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation280.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>B</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{8B} = \frac{1}{a} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>B = \frac{a}{8}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{8Ba}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{8B} \amp = \frac{1}{a}  \\
   \frac{1}{8B} \cdot 8Ba \amp = \frac{1}{a} \cdot 8Ba \\
   a \amp = 8B \\
   \frac{a}{8} \amp = \frac{8B}{8} \\
   \frac{a}{8} \amp = B \\
   B \amp = \frac{a}{8}
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
